If you wish to become an Orthodox Christian I think the most important thing to study is lives of 20th century saints. St. Paisios, St. Porphyrios, St. John of Shanghai, St. Joseph the Hesychast, Fr. Seraphim Rose, etc. They lived very close to us so it's easy to understand them.

Theology and all that is obviously important, but just having knowledge of these great men who lived in our own world and seeing how they thought, their sayings and advice, what they did and how they lived, etc. fills you with love and a spiritual fortitude that is so unshakable.
